{
  "id": "019d285e-83e2-7883-8032-a66d9a92dc67",
  "content": "# Finding: HNSW Index Goes Stale After CLI Ingestion (2026-03-26)\n\n## Problem\n`corvia workspace ingest` writes knowledge JSON files to disk but does NOT rebuild the HNSW vector index. The server's in-memory HNSW only has entries inserted via the REST/MCP API (live writes). After ingestion, the index can have 7 entries while disk has 9,847 files.\n\n## Root Cause\n- `ingest_workspace()` in `workspace.rs` writes files via adapters but never calls `rebuild_index()`\n- `LiteStore::open()` auto-rebuilds only when `next_hnsw_id > 0 && !loaded_from_disk` — this happens on fresh server startup, not while the server is already running\n- The running server never learns about new files written by the CLI\n\n## Impact\n- Search returns results from only ~7 entries instead of ~10k\n- Graph expansion shows no difference (too few entries in index)\n- Benchmark results are meaningless until index is rebuilt\n- Users see correct health findings (reasoner reads files directly) but broken search\n\n## Two Fixes Needed\n\n### 1. Devcontainer startup: detect stale index and rebuild\nAdd a Taskfile task to `post-start` that compares HNSW entry count (via `/api/dashboard/status`) against knowledge file count (via `find .corvia/knowledge -name '*.json' | wc -l`). If they diverge by >10%, trigger `corvia_rebuild_index` via MCP.\n\n### 2. Dashboard: show index staleness indicator\nAdd an `index_stale` boolean and `index_coverage` percentage to the dashboard status endpoint. Compare `entry_count` (HNSW) against file count on disk. Show a warning banner when coverage < 90%.\n\n### Workaround\nAfter ingestion, either restart the server or call:\n```\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8020/mcp -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n  -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"tools/call\",\"params\":{\"name\":\"corvia_rebuild_index\",\"arguments\":{},\"_meta\":{\"confirmed\":true}},\"id\":1}'\n```",
  "source_version": "mcp",
